summary: So my first Comic Con was a blast! I was so nervous at first, and if my mom had not been there with me to say “Hey can she take...
body:
My first Comic Con

So my first Comic Con was a blast! I was so nervous at first, and if my mom had not been there with me to say “Hey can she take a picture with you?” I’d have no pictures. My favorite instance had to be with Spider Gwen. (Pictured first) I was following her around for like 5 whole minutes until my mom got tired of me being shy and just screamed “HEY GWEN MY DAUGHTER LOVES YOU!!” Thanks mom. Like she needed to know that. I also got a Deathstroke picture signed by Mr. Zeck, so that was great. My next Con is probably going to be in Baltimore, so I’m definitely going to go dressed up so I’m more confident. Everyone was so nice and cool! I definitely had fun.

blog.description: Só mais um blog mórbido e frívolo. Aqui compartilho filmes noir, neo-noir, existencialistas, túrbidos e envoltos em um calvário insolúvel.. imagens e bandas de Rock que tem a dor, a solidão e o absurdismo existencial como avanço pessoal e experiência musical sem sucumbir as trevas. Aqui tem um pouco do lado lânguido e distímico de um cara probo, viciado em música, guitarras, animais, livros e família. E que tem como reino sua idílica casa e esposa. É uma página fria e morta. Aqui passo minhas horas desertas..

title: Not All Heroes Wear Capes
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2XwB2Lc

by Roygkid

“I can’t do this, I’m not even the best at taking care of myself!” Peter rambled into the phone. “Maybe somebody else should do it, and I don’t think Mr. Sta—”

“Peter.”

He stopped in an instant.

Happy never called him Peter unless it was extremely important.

——
After the events of Endgame, Peter finds himself babysitting Morgan Stark for the weekend and learns that everyone has their own way of coping through grief.
